</thead>
<tbody><tr>
<td align="left">ADM-01</td>
<td align="left">Log in as Admin and click the Shield icon to enter the Admin Portal.</td>
<td align="left">The Dashboard loads, displaying accurate counts for Registered Students, Lecturers, Courses, and Books.</td>
<td align="left"></td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td align="left">ADM-02</td>
<td align="left">Go to &quot;Manage Courses&quot; tab. Ensure the table has 10 items per page.</td>
<td align="left">Pagination controls (Next/Previous) work without reloading the web page.</td>
<td align="left"></td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td align="left">ADM-03</td>
<td align="left">Click &quot;Add Course&quot;. Fill the form and submit.</td>
<td align="left">The new course is saved to the database and appears in both the Admin table and the public Courses page.</td>
<td align="left"></td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td align="left">ADM-04</td>
<td align="left">Go to &quot;Manage Books&quot;. Click &quot;Add Book&quot; and select a category from the dropdown to prevent syntax errors.</td>
